{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"76092f61-302a-4443-b634-cc763d06eb62","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is an executable. `dotnet run` launches that executable directly and enables the file-watching/hot-reload loop.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest adapter path and **does not** activate the hot reload pipeline, even with the package installed.\n\nSo run:\n\n```bash\nTESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1 dotnet run\n```\n\n(or set the env var separately, then `dotnet run`). It will watch for file changes and re-run affected tests automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a614ad4b-1e0a-4348-be32-31312e5947db","outputTokens":158,"requestId":"5C41:2AF1D1:1DE58E:26004A:69F554E3"},"id":"6c1a5574-39e0-4181-9288-00c4d040a83e","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:35:37.429Z","parentId":"3a745c62-72bd-4204-9ad6-bf7612e55d2f"}
